# pyenv
#   For a library or app, you might want to share your .python-version.
#   Reference: https://github.com/pyenv/pyenv/blob/master/COMMANDS.md#pyenv-version
#.python-version

# pipenv
#   According to Pipfile.lock, it is recommended to include Pipfile.lock in version control.
#   However, in case you run automation, you might want to ignore it.
#Pipfile.lock

# poetry
#   Similar to Pipfile.lock, it is recommended to include poetry.lock in version control.
#   However, in case you run automation, you might want to ignore it.
#poetry.lock

# pdm
#   Similar to Pipfile.lock, it is recommended to include pdm.lock in version control.
#pdm.lock
#   mainline pdm keeps track of physical environments in .pdm-plugins and .pdm-build
.pdm-plugins/
.pdm-build/

